data.title: The dream of a patient in Jungian analysis: a rocky arch, from which steps lead to a river flowing through a lofty tunnel; left, houses on an embankment; beyond, a fjord. Drawing by M.A.C.T., 197-.
data.description: Centre, human beings lit up as by a fire in a cave
data.physicalDescription: 1 drawing : black ink ; sheet 33.8 x 24.7 cm

notes.contents: Drawing by a patient of Dr Alan McGlashan
Possibly related to no. 658132i (summer 1977), which has a similar composition but showing a soft and idyllic scene instead of a harsh and cold one
Related work : M.A.C.T. The dream of a patient in Jungian analysis: a valley, with a meandering path through trees beyond. Drawing by M.A.C.T., 1977. (Wcat)658132i
